This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it deals with the control of a Flapping Wing Micro Air Vehicle (FW MAV). The use of Sliding Mode Control (SMC) theory and adaptive fuzzy control also suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the use of fuzzy logic and adaptation laws suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of adaptation laws and the control of environmental disturbances suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
